(Sobbed grunt, screams)

00:28.896 --> 00:30.095
(Tires squeal)

00:32.767 --> 00:35.667
(Rattles door)

00:38.639 --> 00:40.139
(Gasping, panicky breaths)

00:43.611 --> 00:44.743
(Knocking)

00:45.946 --> 00:48.414
- Oh my God, are you okay?

00:48.482 --> 00:50.482
- (Crying) I don't know.
- Were you in an accident?

00:50.584 --> 00:53.585
- No, it's John.

00:53.687 --> 00:57.022
I think, I-I think I hurt him.

00:57.124 --> 00:59.992
- Lorena, what did you do?

01:02.763 --> 01:04.730
- You might remember me
from the news.

01:04.832 --> 01:06.865
<i> Reporter: Satellite dishes</i>
<i> sprouted like weeds</i>

01:06.967 --> 01:09.601
<i> outside the county courthouse</i>
<i> in Manassas Virginia.</i>

01:09.703 --> 01:11.203
<i> Reporter 2: This is a classic</i>
<i> tabloid story,</i>

01:11.305 --> 01:13.038
<i> it's got sex and blood.</i>

01:13.140 --> 01:14.940
<i> Lorena: Back then,</i>
<i> people laugh at me,</i>

01:15.042 --> 01:16.742
<i> made cruel jokes.</i>

01:16.844 --> 01:18.210
They didn't want to hear
about the truth,

01:18.312 --> 01:20.012
about the abuse I suffered.

01:20.114 --> 01:22.614
<i> Man: Everybody argues, but to</i>
<i> cut a man's penis off for it?</i>

01:22.716 --> 01:24.249
There's no sense in that.

01:24.351 --> 01:27.920
- You might know my name,
but you don't know my story.

01:28.022 --> 01:30.355
<i> I came to live in America</i>
<i> when I was 18.</i>

01:30.458 --> 01:33.592
<i> To me, this was the best</i>
<i> country in the world.</i>

01:33.694 --> 01:35.694
<i> I wanted the American Dream.</i>

01:37.098 --> 01:39.765
<i> Today, I use my maiden name,</i>
<i> Lorena Gallo.</i>

01:39.867 --> 01:42.701
<i> But back then,</i>
<i> I went by a different one.</i>

01:42.803 --> 01:45.671
<i> Back then,</i>
<i> I was Lorena Bobbitt.</i>

01:50.077 --> 01:52.578
<i> To understand the truth</i>
<i> of what really happened,</i>

01:52.680 --> 01:54.680
<i>we need to go back to the night</i>

01:54.782 --> 01:56.748
<i> when I first met</i>
<i> John Wayne Bobbitt.</i>

01:56.851 --> 01:59.318
<i> (Indistinct bar chatter)</i>
<i> - I'm right here!</i>

02:00.521 --> 02:02.254
- Excuse me?

02:02.356 --> 02:03.889
- Well, you're clearly
looking for me.

02:03.991 --> 02:05.491
The most handsome guy
in the place.

02:05.593 --> 02:07.092
- (Laughs)

02:07.194 --> 02:10.062
Uh, no. My friend, Yvonne,
she's out there.

02:11.232 --> 02:13.031
- Okay. Let's go find her.

02:14.168 --> 02:16.835
- Uh, I can't dance.

02:16.937 --> 02:18.770
- That's okay.

02:18.873 --> 02:19.938
(Bottles thunk)

02:20.040 --> 02:22.508
Neither can I.
Who cares?

02:22.610 --> 02:25.110
They'll all be looking at
how pretty you are anyway.

02:25.212 --> 02:27.179
(Indistinct bar chatter,
music plays)

02:27.281 --> 02:31.250
♪♪♪

02:31.352 --> 02:34.019
Your accent,
uh, where is it from?

02:34.121 --> 02:36.455
- Um, I was born in Ecuador,

02:36.557 --> 02:39.558
but my family moved to
Venezuela when I was seven.

02:39.660 --> 02:41.160
You?

02:41.262 --> 02:43.128
- Uh, Upstate New York,
originally.

02:43.230 --> 02:46.465
But I just got back from a tour
in Okinawa.

02:46.567 --> 02:49.701
- You were in the American Army
in Japan?

02:49.803 --> 02:51.370
- I'm a marine.

02:51.472 --> 02:52.938
- What was Japan like?

02:53.040 --> 02:54.706
- It was beautiful.

02:54.808 --> 02:56.074
Lot of history,
food was amazing,

02:56.177 --> 02:57.976
people real friendly.

02:58.078 --> 03:01.079
- That's so wonderful.
I... I only been to the U.S.,

03:01.182 --> 03:03.348
but I want to travel everywhere

03:03.450 --> 03:05.751
and see so many countries.

03:05.853 --> 03:08.187
- Stick with me,
you might just get your wish.

03:09.256 --> 03:10.455
(Small laugh)

03:12.493 --> 03:14.359
What about you?

03:14.461 --> 03:16.295
What are you doing in Virginia?

03:16.397 --> 03:18.063
- I go to school,

03:18.165 --> 03:20.499
and I'm a nanny for a nice
lady, Miss Janna.

03:20.601 --> 03:22.634
- (Laughing)

03:22.736 --> 03:24.036
- You laugh at me.
I know, I know,

03:24.138 --> 03:26.104
my English is so bad.

03:26.207 --> 03:28.307
- No, I'm...

03:28.409 --> 03:30.809
I'm just looking at how
beautiful you are.

03:35.549 --> 03:37.249
How come you don't have
a boyfriend?

03:40.221 --> 03:43.288
Well, looks like we'll have
to change that.

03:45.192 --> 03:46.491
(Chuckles)

03:47.795 --> 03:49.328
(Phone rings)

03:50.731 --> 03:52.397
- Hola?

03:52.499 --> 03:54.066
<i> - Good morning, this is</i>
<i> Corporal John Bobbitt.</i>

03:54.168 --> 03:56.602
<i> May I please speak to Lorena?</i>

03:56.704 --> 03:59.171
- She said you might call.
If you want to see her,

03:59.273 --> 04:01.640
you need to come to the house
so I can meet you.

04:01.742 --> 04:03.141
<i> John: You mean,</i>
<i> like an interview?</i>

04:03.244 --> 04:05.377
- Lorena lives under my roof.

04:05.479 --> 04:07.145
She cannot date anyone
without my permission.

04:07.248 --> 04:08.780
Those are the rules.

04:08.882 --> 04:11.516
<i> - Okay, I'll see you tomorrow.</i>

04:12.753 --> 04:14.453
(Speaking Spanish)

04:16.857 --> 04:19.925
<i> Lorena: He's a soldier</i>
<i> I met last night.</i>

04:20.027 --> 04:23.362
He's really cute,
and he's so nice to me.

04:23.464 --> 04:25.364
- You've only been here
a couple months.

04:25.466 --> 04:27.399
You don't waste any time.

04:27.501 --> 04:30.335
- Oh, it's not like that.
He just ask me to dance,

04:30.437 --> 04:32.738
and then we talk...

04:34.308 --> 04:35.841
I think I like him.

04:35.943 --> 04:37.709
- Only fools rush in, Lorena.

04:39.980 --> 04:42.614
But if he doesn't have three
eyes and a hump on his back,

04:42.716 --> 04:44.883
I'll let you go out with him.
- Oh, thank you, Mrs. Castro!

04:44.985 --> 04:47.853
- But only,
and always, chaperoned.

04:47.955 --> 04:49.621
- (Sighs) He'll think
I'm a child.

04:49.723 --> 04:51.690
<i> - Then he's not worth you.</i>

04:51.792 --> 04:53.625
Your mother would kill me
if I didn't look after you.

04:55.529 --> 04:57.162
- (Sighs)

04:59.199 --> 05:00.365
<i> (Door opens and shuts)</i>

05:03.137 --> 05:04.169
- (Chuckles lightly)

05:05.739 --> 05:08.473
I hired you to be my son's
nanny, not a maid.

05:10.611 --> 05:12.511
- Can I ask you a question?

05:14.181 --> 05:16.648
Ah.

05:16.750 --> 05:19.551
You have this big,
beautiful house,

05:19.653 --> 05:21.019
a nice car,

05:21.121 --> 05:23.522
you own two nail salons--
- About to have three.

05:24.858 --> 05:28.327
- And you do it all alone,
no husband.

05:28.429 --> 05:31.063
It's very impressive.

05:31.165 --> 05:32.998
I want to know,

05:33.100 --> 05:35.467
how do you get that?

05:35.569 --> 05:37.803
- A helluva lotta hard work.

05:39.440 --> 05:41.840
The new store in Centerville
opens next week!

05:44.311 --> 05:47.579
- You know I'm very grateful
for this job,

05:47.681 --> 05:49.214
and... and Kyle,

05:49.316 --> 05:51.817
he's such a good boy,

05:51.919 --> 05:54.720
but... I think--
- You want more.

05:56.423 --> 05:59.358
- Do you think I could ever
work at your nail store?

05:59.460 --> 06:02.327
- What about Kyle?
- Oh, I can do both.

06:02.429 --> 06:04.796
I can work at the nail store
while Kyle is at school,

06:04.898 --> 06:06.865
and then I can come home
and stay with him

06:06.967 --> 06:09.301
until you get back home.

06:09.403 --> 06:11.870
- You know, I think you could,
too.

06:11.972 --> 06:13.372
