(Polaroid camera whirs)

49:32.270 --> 49:34.503
- I'm gonna send these
to the INS.

49:34.605 --> 49:36.105
- What good will that do?

49:36.207 --> 49:38.507
- You can seek asylum
as an abused spouse,

49:38.609 --> 49:40.343
get your permanent green card.

49:40.445 --> 49:42.745
- John says they won't
believe me.

49:42.847 --> 49:44.547
- With these, how can they not?

49:49.454 --> 49:52.088
<i> Lorena: Mercedes sent those</i>
<i> photos to INS,</i>

49:52.190 --> 49:54.590
but they never responded.

49:54.692 --> 49:56.692
(Clapping and cheering)

49:56.794 --> 49:58.761
<i> John's trial was first.</i>

49:58.863 --> 50:01.063
<i> Mine was second.</i>

50:01.165 --> 50:03.499
(Supporters cheer and clap)
Supporter: You got this, John.

50:07.505 --> 50:09.138
<i> Bailiff: Will the defendant</i>
<i> please rise?</i>

50:13.578 --> 50:15.311
<i> Judge: In the case of</i>
<i> the People of Virginia</i>

50:15.413 --> 50:18.848
versus John Wayne Bobbitt,
the jury finds the defendant...

50:20.284 --> 50:22.585
not guilty... (Courtroom cheers)
of marital sexual assault.

50:22.687 --> 50:24.186
(Gavel bangs)

50:24.288 --> 50:26.255
The defendant is free to go.

50:26.357 --> 50:29.158
(Low hum of chatter)

50:32.864 --> 50:35.197
Juror: The jury was persuaded
by Mr. Bobbitt's lawyer

50:35.299 --> 50:37.299
that the case was
too circumstantial.

50:37.402 --> 50:40.536
We couldn't rely on
Mrs. Bobbitt's word alone.

50:40.638 --> 50:42.671
If someone had heard her scream

50:42.774 --> 50:45.074
or there'd been some sort of
bruising,

50:45.176 --> 50:47.510
that'd be more substantive
evidence.

50:47.612 --> 50:49.979
- The law said that evidence

50:50.081 --> 50:52.915
from previous abuse
was inadmissible.

50:54.218 --> 50:56.619
That still upsets me
to this day.

50:58.156 --> 50:59.688
- Get lost!

51:05.096 --> 51:06.762
Would you creeps get a life?!

51:06.864 --> 51:08.297
(Door slams)

51:08.399 --> 51:09.765
<i> News Reporter: In the city</i>
<i> of Manassas, Virginia,</i>

51:09.867 --> 51:11.467
<i> where John Bobbitt</i>
<i> was found not guilty</i>

51:11.569 --> 51:13.569
<i> of sexually assaulting</i>
<i> his wife.</i>

51:13.671 --> 51:16.038
<i> Lorena now faces a charge</i>
<i> of malicious wounding</i>

51:16.140 --> 51:18.774
<i> and could get up to 20 years.</i>

51:18.876 --> 51:20.242
<i> The Washington Post reported</i>
<i> Friday that--</i>

51:20.344 --> 51:21.610
(TV clicks off)

51:23.748 --> 51:25.147
- (Shaky inhale)

51:25.249 --> 51:27.650
It doesn't make any sense.

51:27.752 --> 51:29.652
He admit he hit me.

51:30.721 --> 51:33.856
How can the jury take his side?

51:33.958 --> 51:37.259
- It's such bullshit.

51:37.361 --> 51:39.128
Sweetie, you gotta eat
something.

51:40.231 --> 51:41.831
- I can't. (Sniffling)

51:43.034 --> 51:45.334
All the press out there,

51:46.871 --> 51:48.571
honking their horns,

51:48.673 --> 51:50.072
banging on the door.

51:51.409 --> 51:53.142
I can't sleep.
(Crying)

51:54.345 --> 51:56.212
I'm having nightmares.

51:59.383 --> 52:00.883
- Don't let them win.

52:02.787 --> 52:04.653
Your trial starts in a month.

52:04.755 --> 52:06.856
You need to stay healthy
so that you can fight back

52:06.958 --> 52:08.524
and, and prove your innocence.

52:11.195 --> 52:12.561
- Oh my God... (shaky breath)

52:12.663 --> 52:14.130
if they took his side,

52:14.232 --> 52:16.198
they're not going
to believe me.

52:19.470 --> 52:21.737
Am I going to go to prison?

52:24.842 --> 52:26.041
- (Sighs)

52:30.615 --> 52:31.647
<i> Howard: I'm not gonna lie</i>
<i> to you,</i>

52:31.749 --> 52:34.083
John's acquittal is a blow
to our case.

52:34.185 --> 52:35.885
We need to tweak our strategy
a little bit,

52:35.987 --> 52:38.521
so I've added Ms. Kemler
to our team.

52:41.325 --> 52:42.658
I need you to listen,

52:42.760 --> 52:44.660
and I need you to keep
an open mind.

52:46.964 --> 52:48.831
We'd like to introduce
Battered Women Syndrome

52:48.933 --> 52:51.400
as part of your defense.

52:51.502 --> 52:53.969
<i> Kemler: Now, you should know</i>
<i> it's risky.</i>

52:54.071 --> 52:56.105
It's only been used in court
a couple times

52:56.207 --> 52:57.973
as a viable defense.

52:59.944 --> 53:02.178
- If you think it'll help,
then yes.

53:04.815 --> 53:07.683
- In addition, we'd like
to plead irresistible impulse.

53:09.353 --> 53:12.288
- What does that mean?

53:12.390 --> 53:15.524
- Well, we would argue
that you, the defendant,

53:15.626 --> 53:17.326
couldn't control your actions

53:17.428 --> 53:20.229
as a result of a mental
disorder.

53:20.331 --> 53:22.731
It's a type of insanity plea.

53:24.535 --> 53:26.869
- But I'm not crazy.

53:26.971 --> 53:29.505
- Here, here's the deal, Lorena.

53:29.607 --> 53:31.907
I'm-I'm not blaming you at all,

53:32.009 --> 53:35.444
nor am I judging you
for what you did.

53:35.546 --> 53:37.446
But you already said
you did it,

53:37.548 --> 53:39.648
you confessed to the police.

53:39.750 --> 53:43.085
- If I do something, I take
responsibility for it.

53:43.187 --> 53:45.387
- So, given that,

53:45.489 --> 53:48.090
we need to argue
why you did it.

53:48.192 --> 53:50.326
- Lorena, we need to put you
up on the stand

53:50.428 --> 53:52.795
so that you can tell everyone
what John did to you.

53:57.101 --> 53:59.568
- You want me to...

53:59.670 --> 54:02.304
say this out loud
in front of everyone...

54:03.407 --> 54:05.608
in a courtroom?

54:05.710 --> 54:07.376
<i> I can't do that.</i>

54:17.521 --> 54:19.021
I'm going out with friends
tonight after work,

54:19.123 --> 54:20.990
Mrs. Castro, okay?

54:21.092 --> 54:22.625
Uh, don't wait up,
and don't worry!

54:22.727 --> 54:23.859
<i> Mrs. Castro: Be safe, dear.</i>

54:23.961 --> 54:25.327
- Okay.
(Doorbell rings)

54:25.429 --> 54:27.296
Oh, I'll get it!

54:30.468 --> 54:32.635
(Gasps)

54:32.737 --> 54:34.637
- Hey, you...

54:34.739 --> 54:36.872
- What're you doing here?

54:36.974 --> 54:39.441
- I just drove all night
from New York.

54:39.543 --> 54:42.678
Uh, I wanted to catch you
before you went to work.

54:42.780 --> 54:45.614
- I haven't seen or heard
from you in over a year.

54:45.716 --> 54:47.249
I don't want to talk
to you now.

54:47.351 --> 54:49.985
- Then don't, just...

54:50.087 --> 54:52.087
just listen.

54:52.189 --> 54:53.822
Please?

55:01.599 --> 55:02.898
(Door clicks shut)

55:04.001 --> 55:05.367
- Uh...

55:08.839 --> 55:10.906
I've had a lot of time
to think about...

55:11.008 --> 55:13.475
what's important
since I've been gone.

55:17.281 --> 55:19.915
I got counselling, uh,
from Father McMahon,

55:20.017 --> 55:22.551
and I talked to some older
married couples and...

55:25.189 --> 55:27.089
they said that I should admit
my faults,

55:29.460 --> 55:31.760
uh, beg you for forgiveness,

55:33.164 --> 55:34.997
and uh...

55:37.234 --> 55:40.803
and hope and pray that you...
might uh...

55:43.541 --> 55:45.941
uh, give me another chance.

55:49.380 --> 55:51.046
- I can't just magically erase

55:51.148 --> 55:52.681
everything you did
and said to me.

55:52.783 --> 55:54.416
- Oh, I'm not asking you to.

55:57.321 --> 55:58.721
All I want is for another
chance to make you happy.

55:58.823 --> 56:00.689
I-I know I can do that.

56:02.626 --> 56:05.828
- If we try again,

56:05.930 --> 56:08.664
you have to promise
not to hurt me.

56:10.568 --> 56:12.134
- Promise.

56:12.236 --> 56:13.569
I'm gonna stop drinking,

56:13.671 --> 56:15.671
and I am committed to working
on our marriage.

56:18.476 --> 56:21.043
- Swear to me

56:21.145 --> 56:23.779
that, as my husband,

56:23.881 --> 56:25.514
you won't hurt me.

56:25.616 --> 56:27.816
- On my honor as a Marine.

56:42.199 --> 56:45.167
<i> Lorena: People ask why</i>
<i> I went back with him.</i>

56:45.269 --> 56:49.171
It's difficult to explain who
and what I was back then.

56:49.273 --> 56:51.340
I was 22-years-old,

56:51.442 --> 56:54.410
a Catholic,
a virgin before I met him.

56:54.512 --> 56:56.979
I believed so much in marriage.

56:57.081 --> 56:59.381
<i> When he came back, I thought,</i>

56:59.483 --> 57:02.651
<i> "What if he has changed?"</i>
<i> (John chats with neighbour)</i>

57:02.753 --> 57:05.754
Didn't I owe it to our marriage
to find out?

57:05.856 --> 57:07.523
<i> John: Looks him dead</i>
<i> in the eye...</i>

57:07.625 --> 57:09.291
<i> Lorena: Of course, now I know</i>

57:09.393 --> 57:11.160
<i> that's part of the cycle</i>
<i> of abuse.</i>

57:12.596 --> 57:14.296
Hoping it'll get better,

57:14.398 --> 57:17.399
when really, we know it won't.

57:17.501 --> 57:19.735
- (Laughing)

