- Robbie.
- Hi.

57:24.141 --> 57:25.808
- Nice to see you again.
- I told John

57:25.910 --> 57:27.910
I wouldn't get in the way.
- I'll make up the couch.

57:28.012 --> 57:29.711
It's not very comfortable,

57:29.814 --> 57:31.647
but it should do
for a couple of weeks.

57:31.749 --> 57:34.249
John can you go grab the extra
pair of sheets, please?

57:34.351 --> 57:35.818
- Uh, we were just going
to the hardware store

57:35.920 --> 57:37.786
to get some plywood.
- What for?

57:37.888 --> 57:39.388
- Uh, building a partition,

57:39.490 --> 57:42.991
so Robbie can have
his own room.

57:43.093 --> 57:44.960
- I thought you said it was
just for a couple weeks.

57:45.062 --> 57:46.662
<i> - Dude, you said it was cool</i>

57:46.764 --> 57:48.263
that I could live
with you guys.

57:50.401 --> 57:52.868
- What happened to working on
our marriage?

57:52.970 --> 57:55.137
- We're doing that, baby!
- With Robbie here?

57:55.239 --> 57:57.539
- I-I don't have money for
my own place, man.

57:57.641 --> 57:58.874
- Yeah, don't worry about it.

57:58.976 --> 58:02.077
Lorena's just being bitchy.
- Dude.

58:02.179 --> 58:04.513
Seriously? Uncool.

58:09.186 --> 58:11.687
- You happy now?
You made him leave.

58:11.789 --> 58:14.122
- Is he going to pay the rent?
Buy food? Pay the electric--

58:14.225 --> 58:16.825
- It just doesn't stop
with you, does it?!

58:16.927 --> 58:20.562
Just nag, nag, nag!
At least Robbie can leave.

58:22.433 --> 58:23.799
- So can I.

58:26.170 --> 58:27.669
- Where do you think
you're going?

58:27.771 --> 58:29.438
- Away from you.

58:29.540 --> 58:31.039
It's been six months
since you came back.

58:31.141 --> 58:32.541
You don't have a job,

58:32.643 --> 58:34.476
you flirt with other girls
right under my nose,

58:34.578 --> 58:36.411
you started drinking again,

58:36.514 --> 58:38.447
and you'd rather hang out
with your friends

58:38.549 --> 58:40.382
than spend time with me
in this marriage.

58:41.886 --> 58:43.418
I'm done.

58:44.588 --> 58:46.221
I want a divorce.

58:49.860 --> 58:51.960
- (Deadly calm) You're...

58:52.062 --> 58:53.595
divorcing me.

58:58.569 --> 58:59.935
- (Gasps and screams)

59:00.037 --> 59:02.538
(Suitcases thump)

59:02.640 --> 59:05.207
(Lorena screams)
- I say when we're finished!

59:07.144 --> 59:10.445
Doesn't matter if we're
divorced or separated.

59:10.548 --> 59:12.347
You know I can find you...

59:14.285 --> 59:16.618
and I can screw you
whenever I want.

59:16.720 --> 59:19.988
You're mine, Lorena.

59:20.090 --> 59:22.057
Don't forget it.

59:22.159 --> 59:24.793
- (Gasping for breath)

59:28.465 --> 59:30.198
(Door closes)

59:30.301 --> 59:31.967
(Whimpers)

59:38.576 --> 59:40.042
- Thank you.

59:46.917 --> 59:49.217
Thank you so much
for letting me come over.

59:50.421 --> 59:52.754
I didn't know who else
to talk to.

59:52.856 --> 59:54.489
- You know I'm always here
for you.

59:56.226 --> 59:57.659
Now what's going on?

59:59.363 --> 1:00:00.529
- It's John...

1:00:00.631 --> 1:00:02.264
- Oh...

1:00:04.668 --> 1:00:06.735
I was really hoping it would
work out this time.

1:00:09.540 --> 1:00:11.773
- I know now that
he'll never change.

1:00:13.277 --> 1:00:15.143
The marriage,

1:00:19.083 --> 1:00:20.983
it's over.
(Crying)

1:00:21.085 --> 1:00:23.619
- Oh, honey, I'm so sorry.

1:00:26.390 --> 1:00:28.857
Do you wanna stay here?
The guest room is all made up.

1:00:28.959 --> 1:00:30.826
- It doesn't matter.

1:00:30.928 --> 1:00:33.395
He knows where you live.

1:00:33.497 --> 1:00:34.896
He might try to hurt you, too.

1:00:34.999 --> 1:00:36.865
- Well, I'd like to see him try.

1:00:40.938 --> 1:00:43.939
- He watches...

1:00:44.041 --> 1:00:45.507
every move I make.

1:00:48.412 --> 1:00:51.847
Sometimes I think...
he follows me.

1:00:55.119 --> 1:00:57.386
- How can I help?

1:00:57.488 --> 1:00:59.221
- I want a divorce, but...

1:01:02.059 --> 1:01:05.093
I'm so scared of him,
(Crying)

1:01:06.463 --> 1:01:08.864
of what he'll do
if I try to leave.

1:01:11.101 --> 1:01:13.468
I don't know what to do.

1:01:17.708 --> 1:01:19.141
- I have an idea.

1:01:21.345 --> 1:01:24.446
<i> Lorena: Back then, there was</i>
<i> no national hotline for me</i>

1:01:24.548 --> 1:01:27.182
or any abused women to call.

1:01:27.284 --> 1:01:29.951
We didn't have federal
funding for shelters

1:01:30.054 --> 1:01:32.387
and the Violence Against
Women's Act

1:01:32.489 --> 1:01:35.924
wouldn't become law
until the following year.

1:01:36.026 --> 1:01:38.093
For desperate women,
like me,

1:01:38.195 --> 1:01:40.195
stuck in these situations,

1:01:40.297 --> 1:01:43.331
<i> we were often forced to take</i>
<i> desperate measures</i>

1:01:43.434 --> 1:01:45.500
<i> and protect ourselves</i>

1:01:45.602 --> 1:01:48.036
<i> because the system didn't.</i>

1:01:49.273 --> 1:01:51.139
What're you doing here?

1:01:51.241 --> 1:01:53.575
- Still live here, remember?

1:01:53.677 --> 1:01:56.011
- I thought you said you were
going out with Robbie tonight.

1:01:56.113 --> 1:01:59.548
- Yeah, he's waiting in
the car. I forgot my wallet.

1:01:59.650 --> 1:02:02.617
